4/3/01
  Debug splice point problem:
    - recompile from top of throttle branch => build 1208.
    - set up Divicom, HL
    - set up ad server for stable ads at different resolution

  Even without RC, same resolution, I can see quite severe blocking artifacts
  at splice point, from ad to net.  Seems it has something to do with inserted
  black pictures.

  Noticed that the inter quant matrix is different between ad and black
  pictures.

  Change: insert EOS and RAP between the ad and the first black picture,
          if any.  => build 1209


4/4/01
  Captured a clip badsw1.tsp.  It has severe blocking at capture time using
  DigiTran.  When playing back with HP analyzer, no blocking is seen!

  Do autoSwitch between two HL channels, see some problems with Digitran
  (ripple, white dots and lines, jumps, etc.)!

  Suspect that it may be due to local clock inaccuracy.  Trying using
  input time base mode.

  For TB=1, still sees it, but the frequence is much reduced.

  Adding black pictures does not seem to worsen the situation.  Same result.

  With resolution change, black pictures actually help to give a better
  transition.

  Without black picture, with TB=1, switch are good, except for a very short
  transient state where pictures seems to be in half resolution.
  With TB=2, the bad symptom reappears.


4/5/01
  Noticed that in SeaChange's ad, the random_access_indicator is on for about
  once or twice a second, possible in the I pictures.  This causes HP analyzer
  to complain since we remove PCR at these RA points.  Add code in bufferer
  to also remove the random_access_indicator and discontinuity_indicator
  in AF.

  Noticed that the data_alignment_indicator in PES header may be on, which
  can cause the HP analyzer to think this should start a sequence header,
  since the PMT is not changed for the AD!  Need to clear this flag!

  Turning off EOS won't help Digitran.

  Artifact still seen after clearing data_alignment flag.  HP analyzer still
  complains.

  Change to same rates seems to reduce the problem a little bit, but it still
  exists.

  The HP analyzer compliants are also there when we are bypassing net or ad!

  Turning off audio still does not help Digitran.

  The HP analyzer is complaining about the same thing even for the Divicom
  source!


